<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Continental · Independent American · Pennsylvania Since 1965 · LA Same-Day</p>
    <h1>Continental Refrigerator Repair Los Angeles</h1>
    <p class="lede">Continental Refrigerator commercial service across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Reach-ins, prep tables, undercounters, merchandisers, back-bar coolers. Independent American manufacturer, family-owned since 1965. Mid-premium tier with accessible parts pricing. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href={phoneHref} class="btn btn-primary">☎ Call {phone}</a>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-outline">Book Online</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Continental in the SoCal commercial market</p>
    <h2>Independent American mid-premium, common in independent restaurants and small chains.</h2>

    <p>Continental Refrigerator is the American independent commercial refrigeration manufacturer founded in 1965 in Pennsylvania, family-owned and operated since founding. Continental occupies a specific position in the commercial refrigeration market: a mid-premium tier between True Manufacturing (the largest American independent, with the broadest distribution) and value-tier brands. Continental's pricing has historically been positioned 10-15% below True for comparable units, with build quality similar enough that the brands compete head-to-head in many restaurant kitchen specifications.</p>

    <p>Across SoCal, Continental is common in mid-tier independent restaurants, small restaurant chains, and operations that prioritize total cost of ownership over brand prestige. We service Continental reach-ins, prep tables, undercounters, and merchandisers regularly in our restaurant route across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. Parts availability is good through Continental's authorized distributor network with 3-7 day standard ship on common items.</p>

    <p>Independent ownership matters here. Continental is not part of Ali Group, Welbilt, ITW Food Equipment Group, or any of the major foodservice equipment holding companies. That ownership structure has kept Continental focused on the core commercial refrigeration product line without the corporate-rationalization pressure that affects some brand families. From a service standpoint, this means Continental's product roadmap is consistent and parts compatibility across model years is generally good.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, applied to repair. Same-day response across LA, OC, Ventura. Next-day for Riverside and San Bernardino. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/refrigeration/">commercial refrigeration hub</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Continental product lines we service</p>
    <h2>Series and common service items.</h2>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">Reach-In Refrigerators (1R, 2R, 3R series)</h3>
    <p>Continental's flagship product line: single-door (1R), two-door (2R), and three-door (3R) reach-in refrigerators. Used across restaurant kitchens, school cafeterias, and commercial food service. Common service items: condenser cleaning (every 3-6 months in restaurant duty), evaporator fan motor replacement (year 5-9), thermostat or controller replacement (year 7-10), door gasket replacement (year 4-7), defrost timer service (freezers), refrigerant leak repair (year 8+ on coastal addresses). Compressor replacement window typically year 10-13 for restaurant-duty units.</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">Reach-In Freezers (1F, 2F, 3F series)</h3>
    <p>Single, two, and three-door freezer reach-ins. Same architectural design as the refrigerator series but with freezer-rated refrigerant charge, defrost system, and lower temperature controls. Defrost system service is the additional consideration vs the refrigerator side: defrost timer, termination switch, and heater elements are wear components on commercial freezers. We see defrost-related service most often on year-7+ freezer units.</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">SW / SWF Prep Tables</h3>
    <p>Sandwich and salad prep tables (SW) and prep table freezers (SWF). Pan rail must hold 41°F or below for HACCP compliance during service. Common service items: pan rail temperature failure from dirty condenser plus high-ambient kitchen, thermostat probe drift in the cold pan section, cutting board deterioration on heavy-use units. Service framing matches Delfield prep table (HACCP CCP work, temperature log documentation provided).</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">DL Undercounter Refrigerators</h3>
    <p>DL series single and two-section undercounter refrigerators. Used in bar service, prep stations, sandwich shops. Same architectural service items as reach-ins (condenser, fan, thermostat, gasket) plus the under-counter-specific consideration of condenser airflow restrictions when units are installed in cabinetry without adequate ventilation clearance. We check installation clearance during the diagnostic.</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">MBC Merchandiser Bottle Coolers + BB Back-Bar Series</h3>
    <p>Glass-door bottle coolers (MBC) and back-bar refrigerators (BB) for restaurant bar service and beverage merchandising. Common service items: door heater wire failure (glass fogging), condenser cleaning, evaporator fan motor, controller drift. Bar environment service load is heavier than typical kitchen reach-ins; we recommend monthly condenser cleaning for bar-mounted MBC and BB units in heavy-volume operations.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Common Continental scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Condenser cleaning (every 3-6 months on restaurant-duty units).</strong> $200-280 all-in. About 25-30% of 'not cooling' calls resolve here.</li>
      <li><strong>Evaporator fan motor replacement (year 5-9).</strong> $360-540 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermostat or controller replacement (year 7-10).</strong> $240-380 all-in.</li>
      <li><strong>Door gasket replacement (year 4-7).</strong> $200-360 per door.</li>
      <li><strong>Defrost timer or termination switch (freezers, year 6-9).</strong> $260-440.</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigerant leak repair plus recharge (coastal addresses, year 8+).</strong> $480-820. EPA 608 Universal certified work.</li>
      <li><strong>Compressor replacement (year 10-13 typical).</strong> $1,400-2,400 depending on unit size.</li>
      <li><strong>MBC/BB door heater wire (glass-door units, year 6-9).</strong> $200-340 typical.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Recent Continental service calls</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pasadena cafe, Continental 2R two-door reach-in (2018, year 7)</h3>
        <p>Cabinet at 46°F before lunch service. Condenser loaded with kitchen grease. 45-minute clean, recovery to 38°F within 2 hours. Set restaurant on quarterly PM contract for the 2 Continental units in this kitchen. Total: $120 plus 45 minutes labor = $200.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>WeHo restaurant, Continental SW48 prep table (2017, year 8)</h3>
        <p>Pan rail at 47°F before lunch service, HACCP CCP exceedance. Diagnosed: dirty condenser plus thermostat probe drift in cold pan section. Cleaned condenser, replaced probe, recalibrated. Pan rail at 39°F within 60 minutes. Provided HACCP temperature log documentation. Total: $120 plus $280 part plus 65 minutes labor = $480.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Newport Beach restaurant, Continental 1F freezer (2015, year 10)</h3>
        <p>Cabinet at 12°F, should be at -5°F. Diagnosed: defrost cycle stuck on, defrost heater running continuously even after coil cleared. Defrost termination switch failed. Replaced switch, observed defrost cycle terminate correctly at 18 minutes. Cabinet recovered to -2°F within 90 minutes. Total: $120 plus $260 part plus 50 minutes labor = $420.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Burbank bar, Continental MBC72 back-bar bottle cooler (2019, year 6)</h3>
        <p>Glass doors fogging during bar service, condensation pooling at the bottom. Diagnosed: door heater wire failure on the right door, partial heater wire failure on the left door (slightly less fogging). Replaced both door heater wire assemblies in single visit. Total: $120 plus $480 parts plus 90 minutes labor = $690.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for Continental, and what we don't.</h2>
    <p><strong>We service:</strong> all Continental commercial refrigeration models including 1R/2R/3R reach-ins, 1F/2F/3F freezers, SW/SWF prep tables, DL undercounter, MBC merchandiser bottle coolers, BB back-bar, glass-door merchandisers, chef bases, refrigerated drawers. Restaurant, institutional, and commercial bar applications.</p>
    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new installation as the primary trade (for new installs we partner with commercial kitchen contractors and equipment dealers); custom modification of cabinetry (we service what's installed); residential-scale Continental units (Continental is a commercial brand; if you have a residential unit it's likely a different brand).</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Continental repair costs.</h2>
    <p class="lede">$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</p>
