        <tr><td>Evaporator fan motor replacement</td><td>$360 to $540</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thermostat / controller replacement</td><td>$240 to $380</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (per door)</td><td>$200 to $360</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Defrost timer or termination switch</td><td>$260 to $440</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Refrigerant leak repair + recharge</td><td>$480 to $820</td></tr>
        <tr><td>MBC/BB door heater wire (per door)</td><td>$200 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (1R / 2R / DL)</td><td>$1,400 to $2,000</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (3R / 3F)</td><td>$2,000 to $2,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Quarterly PM contract</td><td>Quote-based</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts and labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07 · Why us for Continental</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What separates our Continental service.</h2>
    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>Common parts on the van.</strong> Thermostats, evaporator fan motors, door gaskets, defrost components for the major Continental model lines.</li>
      <li><strong>Authorized parts coordination.</strong> Continental's distributor network with 3-7 day standard ship on specialty items.</li>
      <li><strong>HACCP temperature log documentation.</strong> Every commercial service call.</li>
      <li><strong>Repair-vs-replace honest math.</strong> Mid-premium tier means repair-justified through year 12-13 typically; we tell you when replacement is the better economic call.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410 plus CSLB C-38 Refrigeration scope.</strong> Verifiable.</li>
      <li><strong>Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura.</strong> Next-day for Riverside and San Bernardino. Phones answered 24/7.</li>
      <li><strong>BBB A+ verifiable.</strong> See our <a href="/credentials/licensed/">license credentials</a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
